## ABSOLUTE RULES

```
1.  Gemini Flash for everything now — one line change to swap later
2.  Credit consumed on first question delivery — never on creation
3.  Candidate turn saved BEFORE AI generation — data never lost
4.  Deepgram token generated server-side — API key never in browser
5.  Activity expectedAnswer NEVER sent to client — ever
6.  Score inflation is a bug — system prompt enforces honesty
7.  Recovery must work — page refresh during ACTIVE resumes seamlessly
8.  Failed interview shows partial conversation — never a blank screen
9.  Code editor opens/closes per activity type — never permanently open
10. One question visible at a time during ACTIVE — full history on COMPLETED only
11. No Ably anywhere — Vercel AI SDK streams, polling detects report ready
12. generateObject() for structured AI responses — no manual JSON parsing
13. streamText() for interview turns — tokens flow directly to client
14. Report generation is async BullMQ job — never blocks the interview completion
```

